{{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | honorific-prefix = [[The Right Reverend]] | name = Guy Erwin | title = Bishop | image = Guy Erwin 09 2016.jpg | image_size = 220 | alt = | caption = Erwin in September 2016 | church = [[Evangelical Lutheran Church in America]] | archdiocese = | diocese = | see = Southwest California Synod |spouse = {{marriage|Rob Flynn|August 2013}} | alma_mater = {{unbulleted list | [[Harvard University]] | [[Yale University]]}} | religion = [[Lutheran]] | birth_date = 1958 | birth_place = [[Pawhuska, Oklahoma|Pawhuska]], [[Oklahoma]], U.S. | residence = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S. | birth_name = | term = October 10, 2013 – present | predecessor = Dean Nelson }}
'''R. Guy Erwin''' (born 1958) is an American [[Lutheranism|Lutheran]] [[bishop]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Sherman |first=Bill |date=June 10, 2013 |title=Lutheran church's first gay bishop has area ties |url=http://www.tulsaworld.com/news/religion/lutheran-church-s-first-gay-bishop-has-area-ties/article_1fef71ef-1f75-5c61-a00e-30adb2034627.html |newspaper=Tulsa World |issn=2330-7234 |access-date=June 29, 2017}}</ref> He was elected in 2013 to a six-year term as bishop of the Southwest California Synod of the [[Evangelical Lutheran Church in America]] (ELCA).<ref>http://theguibordcenter.org/about/advisory-council/name/guy-erwin/</ref>
Erwin is the first [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native American]] bishop elected to office in the ELCA, and is a member of the [[Osage Nation]]. He is also the first openly gay bishop in the ELCA, and has lived in a committed same-sex relationship for 20 years. He and Rob Flynn were married in August 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://socalsynod.org/news/the-rev-dr-r-guy-erwin-elected-bishop/|title = The Rev. Dr. R. Guy Erwin Elected Bishop|publisher = Southwest California Synod, ELCA|author = Press release|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://archive.is/20130619133438/http://socalsynod.org/news/the-rev-dr-r-guy-erwin-elected-bishop/|archivedate = 2013-06-19|df = }}</ref>
Erwin received a [[Bachelor of Arts]] degree from [[Harvard College]] in 1980. He holds the [[Master of Arts]], [[Master of Philosophy]], and [[Doctor of Philosophy]] degrees from [[Yale University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://divinity.yale.edu/news/about-people-august-2013|title=About, People - August 2013 - Yale Divinity School|website=divinity.yale.edu|accessdate=8 November 2018}}</ref> From 1993 to 1999 he was lecturer in Church history in the [[Yale Divinity School]] (YDS), where he taught History of Western Christianity as well as courses on [[Martin Luther]], the [[Pietism|Pietists]] and other specialities. During the 2006–2007 academic year he was visiting professor at YDS while on sabbatical from [[California Lutheran University]] where he has taught since 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scpr.org/programs/take-two/2013/06/07/32130/rev-guy-erwin-elected-first-openly-gay-bishop-evan/|title=Rev. Guy Erwin on becoming the Evangelical Lutheran Church's first openly gay bishop|first=Southern California Public|last=Radio|date=7 June 2013|publisher=|accessdate=8 November 2018}}</ref>
