'''Pranahita Pushkaralu''' is a festival of [[Pranahita River|River Pranahita]] normally occurs once in 12 years. The [[Pushkaram]] is observed for a period of 12 days from the time of entry of [[Jupiter]] into [[Pisces (astrology)|Pisces]] (''Meena'' rasi).<ref>{{cite book |author=Roshen Dalal |title=Hinduism: An Alphabetical Guide |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zrk0AwAAQBAJ&pg=PT921 |date=18 April 2014 |publisher=Penguin Books Limited |isbn=978-81-8475-277-9 |pages=921–}}</ref>
