The title '''Rosh mesivta''' (alt. Rosh metivta<ref>"He was previously RAM (Rosh Metivta) at ..." {{cite web |title=The Pardes Kollel Experience - These and Those |url=https://theseandthose.pardes.org/2014/02/03/the-pardes-kollel-experience |date=February 3, 2014}}</ref>), abbreviated as Ram,<ref>"... ram (for rosh mesivta, 'head of ...'){{cite book |title=Dictionary of Jewish Usage: A Guide to the Use of Jewish Terms |url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=0742543870 |isbn=0742543870 |author=Sol Steinmetz |date=2005}}</ref><ref>QUOTE: (There was also some talk in the Yeshiva "in those days" about how "the Ram" (as he was often called - standing for Rosh Mesivta) ... {{cite book |title=The Legacy of Maran Rav Aharon Kotler: A Vivid Portrait of ... |url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=158330875X |isbn=158330875X |author=Yitzchok Dershowitz |date=2005}}</ref> is a term in Jewish education for a leading figure in an educational institution. The term has a long history, going back many centuries.<ref>{{cite book |title=Codex Judaica: Chronological Index of Jewish History|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=0967037832 |isbn=0967037832|author=Mattis Kantor |date=2005}}</ref>
The role is comparable to a dean in a university.<ref>".. ROSH MESIVTA: the dean of a MESIVTA." {{cite book|title=There is No Such Thing as Coincidence, And Other Stories|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1583306153|isbn=1583306153|author=Barukh ben David Lev|date=2003}}</ref> Just as a chancellor outranks a dean<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.english-test.net/forum/ftopic60452.html |title=rector vs chancellor vs president}} - citing Oxford University.</ref> a Rosh yeshiva, when both exist, is higher.<ref>appointed Rosh Yeshiva... was Rosh Mesivta. {{cite newspaper |newspaper=5 Towns Jewish Times |title=Yeshivat Torah V'avodah Appoints New Rosh Yeshiva |url=http://5tjt.com/yeshivat-torah-vavodah-appoints-new-rosh-yeshiva |date=June 8, 2017}}</ref><ref>R... next moved to the Telshe yeshiva as a rosh mesivta ... (rosh yeshiva) left the Telshe yeshiva and R... replaced him as rosh yeshiva. {{cite web |url= http://www.daat.ac.il/daat/chinuch/mosdot/telz-2.htm|script-title=Yeshivas Telz |first= Mordechai|last=Gifter|authorlink = Mordechai Gifter| year= 2003|publisher = [[Herzog College]]|language = Hebrew|trans-title=Telz Yeshiva | accessdate = 15 February 2011}}</ref>
