{{use dmy dates|date=March 2018}} {{Infobox political party |name = Bnei Brit HaHadasha |native_name = בני ברית החדשה |country = Israel |colorcode = |logo = |leader = Bishara Shilyan |foundation = 10 July 2013 |seats1_title = [[Knesset]] |seats1 = {{Composition bar|0|120|hex=}} |ideology = {{unbulleted list | [[Arab Christian]] interests | Pro-[[two-state solution]]}} |position = [[Centre-left politics|Centre-left]] |headquarters = |international = |colours = |website = |symbol = }} The '''Sons of the New Testament''' ({{Lang-he|בני ברית החדשה}}, ''Bnei Brit HaHadasha'') is a political party in [[Israel]].
==History== The party was established in 2013 with the aim of representing the interests of [[Arab Christians|Arabic-speaking Christians]] in Israel. The party encourages full integration of [[Arabophone]] Christians into Israeli society, the [[two-state solution]], and enlistment of Arabophone Christians into the [[Israel Defense Forces]]. It was founded by Bishara Shilyan, a 58-year-old sea captain from Nazareth. One of the reasons for founding the party is the belief that the existing Arab parties predominantly serve Muslim interests.<ref>{{cite news |last=Schwartz |first=Sharona |url=http://www.theblaze.com/stories/2013/07/10/arab-spring-prompts-israeli-christians-to-break-from-muslim-political-parties-and-form-new-movement/ |title='Arab Spring' Prompts Israeli Christians to Break from Muslim Political Parties and Form New Movement |publisher=TheBlaze |date=10 June 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2015}}</ref> Israel's Arabophone Christians are predominantly [[Melkite Greek Catholic Church|Melkite Greek]] and [[Roman Catholic]] and represent a minority within the broader Arab population of the country.<ref name="toi">{{cite news |last1=Berman |first1=Lazar |last2=Miller |first2=Elhanan |url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/new-christian-arab-party-calls-for-idf-enlistment/ |title=New Christian Arab party calls for IDF enlistment |newspaper=The Times of Israel |date=10 July 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2015}}</ref><ref name="it">{{cite web |last=Jones |first=Ryan |url=http://www.israeltoday.co.il/NewsItem/tabid/178/nid/23972/Default.aspx?hp=article_title |title=New Arab Christian party announced in Israel |work=Israel Today |date=10 July 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2015}}</ref>
The party's founder, Shilyan, has also said he wants to build a {{convert|30.5|m|ft|adj=on}} tall statue of [[Jesus]] (modelled on [[Christ the Redeemer (statue)|Rio de Janeiro's Christ the Redeemer statue)]] on top of a mountain in [[Nazareth]]. He said the purpose of the statue would be to prevent Nazareth's Christian heritage from being eroded. The town's Christian population has been steadily decreasing relative to its Muslim population.<ref name="statue">{{cite news |last=Bohon |first=Dave |url=http://www.thenewamerican.com/world-news/asia/item/17260-plans-shaping-up-for-100-foot-jesus-statue-in-muslim-dominated-Nazareth |title=Plans Shaping up for 100-foot Jesus Statue in Muslim-Dominated Nazareth |work=The New American |date=27 December 2013 |accessdate=24 June 2015}}</ref>
